org.locationtech.geowave.core.geotime.store.query

Class ExplicitSpatialQuery

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.query.constraints.BasicQuery
      • org.locationtech.geowave.core.store.query.constraints.BasicQueryByClass
        • org.locationtech.geowave.core.geotime.store.query.ExplicitSpatialQuery
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Persistable, QueryConstraints
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExplicitSpatialTemporalQuery, IndexOnlySpatialQuery

    public class ExplicitSpatialQuery
extends BasicQueryByClass
    The Spatial Query class represents a query in two dimensions. The constraint that is applied represents an intersection operation on the query geometry.

        public List<MultiDimensionalNumericData> getIndexConstraints(Index index)
        Description copied from interface: QueryConstraints
        Return a set of constraints to apply to the primary index based on the indexing strategy used. The ordering of dimensions within the index stategy must match the order of dimensions in the numeric data returned which will represent the constraints applied to the primary index for the query.
